00:36:06.620 --> 00:36:07.260
What do you think

00:36:07.620 --> 00:36:08.900
of Mr. Wang?

00:36:11.180 --> 00:36:11.900
Mr. Wang?

00:36:15.340 --> 00:36:16.340
Ms. Tan's friend.

00:36:17.980 --> 00:36:18.740
Wang Zeyuan?

00:36:19.140 --> 00:36:19.340
Yes.

00:36:19.340 --> 00:36:20.060
What about him?

00:36:21.620 --> 00:36:22.340
I just think

00:36:22.620 --> 00:36:24.900
he and Ms. Tan look good together.

00:36:25.340 --> 00:36:26.460
And he's young and accomplished.

00:36:27.260 --> 00:36:28.980
I heard he's pursued Ms. Tan
for a long time.

00:36:30.140 --> 00:36:31.420
Now they're finally together.

00:36:32.740 --> 00:36:33.260
Is that so?

00:36:36.620 --> 00:36:37.580
It seems that way,

00:36:38.140 --> 00:36:38.860
probably.

00:36:41.700 --> 00:36:42.260
No idea.

00:36:51.020 --> 00:36:52.780
Are you feeling more relaxed now?

00:36:54.540 --> 00:36:56.340
Finished the noodles, now sipping tea.

00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:58.300
You really know how to plan things.

00:36:58.420 --> 00:36:59.180
You understand how to live.

00:37:00.420 --> 00:37:01.580
This place is nice, right?

00:37:04.100 --> 00:37:04.540
You know what?

00:37:04.540 --> 00:37:05.540
I lived in a pretty remote area

00:37:05.540 --> 00:37:07.780
when I was little.

00:37:08.060 --> 00:37:08.980
I always thought

00:37:09.340 --> 00:37:10.460
that when I grew up,

00:37:10.660 --> 00:37:11.460
I would

00:37:11.660 --> 00:37:14.060
live in a lively, bustling place.

00:37:14.580 --> 00:37:15.900
I'm a bit different from you.

00:37:16.820 --> 00:37:18.420
My work pace

00:37:18.660 --> 00:37:19.900
is already very fast.

00:37:20.380 --> 00:37:22.180
So when I rest, I prefer

00:37:22.540 --> 00:37:24.380
to slow down. Like driving around.

00:37:25.020 --> 00:37:26.780
Driving for a ride-sharing service?

00:37:27.580 --> 00:37:28.060
Yeah.

00:37:28.860 --> 00:37:29.740
I drive for the ride-sharing service

00:37:29.740 --> 00:37:31.660
to chat with passengers.

00:37:32.100 --> 00:37:33.060
Talk about all sorts of things.

00:37:34.380 --> 00:37:35.580
Those passengers

00:37:35.580 --> 00:37:37.820
who get your luxury car

00:37:38.340 --> 00:37:39.300
are pretty lucky.

00:37:39.580 --> 00:37:41.140
Actually, among those,

00:37:41.620 --> 00:37:42.340
some

00:37:42.340 --> 00:37:44.380
are genuinely well-off,

00:37:44.660 --> 00:37:46.220
while others

00:37:47.140 --> 00:37:48.140
might be doing it for face.

00:37:48.740 --> 00:37:50.660
Their demeanor
before and after getting in the car

00:37:50.660 --> 00:37:51.660
can be very different.

00:37:51.860 --> 00:37:52.660
It's really interesting.

00:37:52.860 --> 00:37:53.780
I enjoy observing them.

00:37:54.260 --> 00:37:56.060
But I'm not doing it for face.

00:37:56.060 --> 00:37:57.700
I purely do it for comfort.

00:37:57.860 --> 00:37:59.380
You were so genuine that day.

00:38:00.860 --> 00:38:01.580
Very genuine?

00:38:04.540 --> 00:38:06.420
So do you live alone now,

00:38:06.420 --> 00:38:07.740
or with your parents?

00:38:08.100 --> 00:38:09.300
I've always lived alone.

00:38:10.180 --> 00:38:11.300
My parents passed away early.

00:38:11.540 --> 00:38:12.860
Later, I had some luck.

00:38:12.860 --> 00:38:13.860
Started some businesses

00:38:13.860 --> 00:38:14.860
and made some money.

00:38:15.180 --> 00:38:16.980
I also made some friends in real estate.

00:38:17.540 --> 00:38:19.460
Now we have an investment company.

00:38:20.060 --> 00:38:20.820
If I said I'm a fairy,

00:38:20.820 --> 00:38:21.420
would you believe me?

00:38:21.540 --> 00:38:22.180
I'd believe it.

00:38:22.940 --> 00:38:24.860
Were you single when you descended?

00:38:25.660 --> 00:38:27.420
How do you know I'm single?

00:38:28.980 --> 00:38:31.300
The whole world
heard you shouting about it that day.

00:38:36.020 --> 00:38:36.660
Then

00:38:37.820 --> 00:38:38.380
what about you?

00:38:40.220 --> 00:38:41.460
I haven't been
in a relationship for years.

00:38:43.020 --> 00:38:44.300
Never met the right person.

00:38:46.540 --> 00:38:48.180
Love is something

00:38:49.020 --> 00:38:50.060
you can't force.

00:38:50.940 --> 00:38:51.700
Just go with the flow.

00:38:53.860 --> 00:38:55.180
But I still envy those

00:38:55.180 --> 00:38:56.100
who have love.

00:38:59.220 --> 00:38:59.980
I just feel like

00:38:59.980 --> 00:39:01.780
love isn't in the cards for me.

00:39:02.740 --> 00:39:04.420
My past relationships...

00:39:09.260 --> 00:39:10.060
You got hurt?

00:39:13.700 --> 00:39:14.940
Actually, I don't think

00:39:15.940 --> 00:39:17.620
love itself hurts people.

00:39:18.860 --> 00:39:20.420
What hurts us is probably

00:39:21.300 --> 00:39:22.420
the person within that love.

00:39:22.900 --> 00:39:23.620
But when we meet

00:39:23.620 --> 00:39:24.820
the right person,

00:39:25.620 --> 00:39:26.820
then love can be good.

00:39:32.980 --> 00:39:33.820
You're right, Mr. Wu.

00:39:34.820 --> 00:39:35.820
Don't call me Mr. Wu.

00:39:35.900 --> 00:39:37.180
Makes it sound like
we're doing business.

00:39:37.460 --> 00:39:37.940
Call me Zu.

00:39:39.620 --> 00:39:40.140
Zu.

00:39:48.140 --> 00:39:48.820
Cheers.

00:40:16.860 --> 00:40:17.260
Here.

00:40:22.900 --> 00:40:23.340
Take it slow.

